    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A Buddhist family altar or shrine found usually in Japanese homes, but also in temples. Generally a freestanding cabinet with two doors, in which are kept memorial items of dead ancestors and representations of divinities. Incense, candles, and flowers are offered at the butsudan in daily rituals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
